column5: This was sent to me last year from a buddy of mine who lives in Terrace Bay...this calf wandered into the mechanical shop at the pulp and paper mill.  It was re-united with it's mother through the MNR    Jason
I see the cute part...but what's that thing with the long ears! LOL
yes i see what you mean...  oh ya cute little fella

That is one cute lil fella..... I just can't get over the fact that we hunters even consider takin them when their that young....I personally have never had the opportunity to harvest a calf and Ive always questioned myself if when the time came, I could even pull the trigger....I think not....  Cheers !!
If I brough the girl, oh i meen the moose home, would that be poaching
